00:18:18.960 --> 00:18:20.480
is really important to this guy.

00:18:20.480 --> 00:18:23.210
It's important to everyone.

00:18:23.210 --> 00:18:25.920
And I can't stress this, we
stressed it in the first talk

00:18:25.920 --> 00:18:26.690
as well.

00:18:26.690 --> 00:18:31.870
But sign in with Cloud Save
is really, really important.

00:18:31.870 --> 00:18:36.540
Because people are often
buying things within your game.

00:18:36.540 --> 00:18:38.830
And if they feel like
their purchases are

00:18:38.830 --> 00:18:41.270
going to be lost because
they lost their phone,

00:18:41.270 --> 00:18:43.800
or because they upgrade
to a new device,

00:18:43.800 --> 00:18:46.460
that makes them less
likely to want to purchase.

00:18:46.460 --> 00:18:48.330
And we actually have
this anecdotally.

00:18:48.330 --> 00:18:51.410
So one of our good
friends actually

00:18:51.410 --> 00:18:54.059
kept getting request
after request

00:18:54.059 --> 00:18:56.100
after request from gamers,
please, please, please

00:18:56.100 --> 00:18:57.400
put in Cloud Save.

00:18:57.400 --> 00:18:59.380
They integrated it, and boom.

00:18:59.380 --> 00:19:03.240
The next day they saw
massive increases in sales.

00:19:03.240 --> 00:19:05.700
People were literally
waiting for that.

00:19:05.700 --> 00:19:08.420
So again, Cloud Save is
really, really important.

00:19:08.420 --> 00:19:10.260
But for these guys,
we really have

00:19:10.260 --> 00:19:13.480
anything for social
discovery, until last week.

00:19:13.480 --> 00:19:14.870
So this is cool.

00:19:14.870 --> 00:19:18.240
We've actually added a
new feature to play games.

00:19:18.240 --> 00:19:19.670
Which is game gifts.

00:19:19.670 --> 00:19:21.350
Which is exciting.

00:19:21.350 --> 00:19:23.350
A lot of people have asked
us, how do I do this?

00:19:23.350 --> 00:19:24.933
In fact there are
people who are using

00:19:24.933 --> 00:19:26.707
multiplayer that try to do this.

00:19:26.707 --> 00:19:28.790
This is really, if you
want to actually get people

00:19:28.790 --> 00:19:31.270
into the social
graph of your game,

00:19:31.270 --> 00:19:33.030
this is actually a
great way of doing it.

00:19:33.030 --> 00:19:34.450
I'm going to talk about it.

00:19:34.450 --> 00:19:36.675
So here's how it actually looks.

00:19:36.675 --> 00:19:39.050
And I'm actually going to put
some code up on the screen,

00:19:39.050 --> 00:19:41.216
since I know a bunch of you
are actually developers.

00:19:41.216 --> 00:19:44.210
So don't be scared.

00:19:44.210 --> 00:19:46.330
And of course an extra
life looks like a mushroom.

00:19:46.330 --> 00:19:50.460
It's the universal
symbol for an extra life.

00:19:50.460 --> 00:19:52.130
So here's what the
flow looks like.

00:19:52.130 --> 00:19:54.190
OK, first of all,
someone in the game

00:19:54.190 --> 00:19:56.570
says, I want to send an extra
life to one of my friends.

00:19:56.570 --> 00:19:59.254
And this is the code
that you use to do that.

00:19:59.254 --> 00:20:00.920
And it's really,
really straightforward.

00:20:00.920 --> 00:20:03.545
You say, give me an
intent, start an activity.

00:20:03.545 --> 00:20:08.000
And that Intent contains a
payload of whatever you want,

00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:10.625
how long you want to
live, in days, an icon,

00:20:10.625 --> 00:20:13.142
and a description.

00:20:13.142 --> 00:20:13.725
And that's it.

00:20:13.725 --> 00:20:15.180
That's all you have
to do to actually send

00:20:15.180 --> 00:20:17.690
a gift, one line of code,
two lines of code, actually.

00:20:17.690 --> 00:20:19.620
I lied.

00:20:19.620 --> 00:20:21.200
And then, from
there, we actually

00:20:21.200 --> 00:20:22.980
pop up this screen
saying, hey, who

00:20:22.980 --> 00:20:24.500
do you want to send a gift to?

00:20:24.500 --> 00:20:25.740
In this screen it's me.

00:20:25.740 --> 00:20:27.320
Everyone send gifts to me.

00:20:27.320 --> 00:20:30.130
That's a subtle hint.

00:20:30.130 --> 00:20:32.020
Finally it goes into our cloud.

00:20:32.020 --> 00:20:36.300
And then from there we
actually send a notification.

00:20:36.300 --> 00:20:38.840
In this case from me to me.

00:20:38.840 --> 00:20:40.480
And then, aha!

00:20:40.480 --> 00:20:42.690
I get an aggregate list of
all the gifts and requests

00:20:42.690 --> 00:20:43.606
that people have made.

00:20:43.606 --> 00:20:44.830
So this is not just gifts.

00:20:44.830 --> 00:20:48.510
This actually shows other
social interactions as well.

00:20:48.510 --> 00:20:50.440
And then finally I
can accept the gift.

00:20:50.440 --> 00:20:51.910
And then, if the
game's installed,

00:20:51.910 --> 00:20:53.743
I just go to the game
and I accept the gift.

00:20:53.743 --> 00:20:55.440
Otherwise I go to
Google Play Store,

00:20:55.440 --> 00:20:57.060
and then I can install the game.

00:20:57.060 --> 00:20:58.700
So I can then accept the gift.

00:20:58.700 --> 00:21:00.820
And then this is what
actually happens.

00:21:00.820 --> 00:21:04.540
So after I sign in, what
I'm going to want to do

00:21:04.540 --> 00:21:06.530
is actually get any
requests that are pending.

00:21:06.530 --> 00:21:08.530
And that's how I actually
go to accept the gift.

00:21:08.530 --> 00:21:09.700
Again, not a lot of code here.

00:21:09.700 --> 00:21:11.449
If you're already using
Play Game Services

00:21:11.449 --> 00:21:14.370
this is just like
one extra line.

00:21:14.370 --> 00:21:17.200
And then I actually
handle the requests.

00:21:17.200 --> 00:21:19.610
And then finally, it comes back.

00:21:19.610 --> 00:21:21.700
It calls me back and says,
yes indeed, these gifts

00:21:21.700 --> 00:21:22.640
have been accepted.

00:21:22.640 --> 00:21:25.330
And I can put whatever code
I have right here in order

00:21:25.330 --> 00:21:25.830
to accept.

00:21:25.830 --> 00:21:27.160
And I can do just
more than gifts,

00:21:27.160 --> 00:21:28.201
I can actually do wishes.

00:21:28.201 --> 00:21:30.735
So you can see this little
guy here is going help!

00:21:30.735 --> 00:21:33.000
So I can also ask for
extra life, for example.

00:21:33.000 --> 00:21:34.242
Or ask for help.

00:21:34.242 --> 00:21:35.950
So I can actually send
a gift to someone,

00:21:35.950 --> 00:21:40.420
or I can do a
request for a gift.

00:21:40.420 --> 00:21:44.860
So once again,
one up successful.

00:21:44.860 --> 00:21:46.210
All right.

00:21:46.210 --> 00:21:48.735
Now the other thing, this is
kind of a complicated flow.

00:21:48.735 --> 00:21:50.710
So you can actually
register for a note

00:21:50.710 --> 00:21:54.230
to be notified that gifts
have come to your app.

00:21:54.230 --> 00:21:57.220
So you'll just get a
notification when they come in.

00:21:57.220 --> 00:22:01.440
And you can show the request
inbox from within your game.

00:22:01.440 --> 00:22:03.570
But you can actually
use the gifting system

00:22:03.570 --> 00:22:04.930
for much more than just that.

00:22:04.930 --> 00:22:09.294
You can also use it to
trade items between players.

00:22:09.294 --> 00:22:10.710
Because I didn't
actually show you

00:22:10.710 --> 00:22:14.322
everything when I showed
you this first graph.

00:22:14.322 --> 00:22:15.780
There's something
missing, which is

00:22:15.780 --> 00:22:17.350
that after you've
accepted the gift,

00:22:17.350 --> 00:22:19.830
you actually get a
notification back saying,

00:22:19.830 --> 00:22:21.470
yes, this person
accepted the gift.

00:22:21.470 --> 00:22:23.500
Which means you can
use the same gifting

00:22:23.500 --> 00:22:25.739
system to actually
do things like trade.

00:22:25.739 --> 00:22:28.280
So instead of accepting the gift
here, I could have said hey,

00:22:28.280 --> 00:22:29.720
do you want to make this trade?

00:22:29.720 --> 00:22:32.581
And then it actually says
sure, and now it trades it.

00:22:32.581 --> 00:22:34.580
You can even have it go
through multiple rounds.

00:22:34.580 --> 00:22:36.140
You could actually
have hey, no I

00:22:36.140 --> 00:22:38.390
don't want to accept
that gift, so I say no.

00:22:38.390 --> 00:22:40.794
But then I actually want to
say but I'll do this instead.

00:22:40.794 --> 00:22:42.710
And you can actually
have these really complex

00:22:42.710 --> 00:22:45.150
social interactions going
in loops, between people

00:22:45.150 --> 00:22:48.710
negotiating for gifts that they
might want to have or trade.

00:22:48.710 --> 00:22:51.000
